sql:
SELECT fund_id
FROM performance
WHERE CAST(REPLACE(percentage_return, ',', '.') AS REAL) = (
  SELECT MAX(CAST(REPLACE(percentage_return, ',', '.') AS REAL))
  FROM performance
);

external_knowledge:
- 'average return on investment' refers to the average percentage return of the funds; 
- 'type of asset' corresponds to the asset class; 
- 'verifiable returns' means average percentage return is not null.
